definitions.definition: The condition or state of having won a battle or competition , or having succeeded in an effort ; ( countable ) an instance of this.
examples: It was a great victory on the battlefield.

definitions.definition: Alternative letter-case form of Victory ( “ ( uncountable ) the Roman goddess of victory , the counterpart of the Greek goddess Nike ; also ( countable ) , an artistic depiction of her, chiefly as a winged woman ” ) .
